I think that this upgrade from MIUI 6 has

00:00:48.140 --> 00:00:54.190
made the phone a lot smoother. At even the
latest version of MIUI 6, I was seeing a lot

00:00:54.190 --> 00:00:59.250
of stuttering here and there but with the
MIUI 7, the lagginess has been minimized.

00:00:59.250 --> 00:01:04.220
In the notification drawer, The icon style
has also changed and they have a small animation

00:01:04.220 --> 00:01:09.220
now. Also, the brightness toggle has been
configured like what we have seen in Android

00:01:09.220 --> 00:01:14.000
Lollipop and I quiet like it.
Another feature which has been added to the

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:18.720
phone is the parental control. Through this
feature, a parent can configure which app

00:01:18.720 --> 00:01:24.320
would be accessible to their children. Not
quiet useful for me, but can be useful for

00:01:24.320 --> 00:01:30.110
some of you guys.
Also, the way apps open and terminate has

00:01:30.110 --> 00:01:36.130
also changed. It is now more of a lollipop
style gesture and that again makes the device

00:01:36.130 --> 00:01:39.580
look quiet snappier.
Though some things have been changed in the

00:01:39.580 --> 00:01:44.430
ROM, the camera UI is still not changed. But
this is not the final version and they may

00:01:44.430 --> 00:01:50.320
release the new UI on 19th August in their
event in Delhi.

00:01:50.320 --> 00:01:55.650
